nwriter, stage director, and a celebrated painter. In 1998, Gao was granted French citizenship.<\/p><p>Gao's drama is considered to be fundamentally <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Theatre_of_the_Absurd\" title=\"The Theatre of the Absurd\" class=\"mw-redirect\">absurdist<\/a> in nature and avant-garde in his native China. His prose works tend to be less celebrated in China but are highly regarded elsewhere in Europe and the West.<\/p>","name":"Gao Xingjian","place_of_birth":"Ganzhou , Jiangxi, China","place_of_death":null,"text":"Gao Xingjian ,  born in China , Literature, 2000","year":2000.0}